    <thetext>Description of problem: if one uses xfce4-panel and its xfce4-xkb-plugin in isolation from the whole Xfce then click on &quot;Keyboard settings&quot; does nothing unless xfce4-settings manually installed.


Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 
xfce4-panel-4.12.0-5.fc24.i686
xfce4-xkb-plugin-0.7.1-6.fc24.i686


How reproducible: always


Steps to Reproduce:
1. Ensure you have xfce4-panel but have no Xfce in a whole
2. Launch xfce4-panel
3. Add &quot;Keyboard layouts&quot; applet
4. Right click on it
5. Click on &quot;Keyboard settings&quot; menu item

Actual results: nothing


Expected results: keyboard settings dialog window


Additional info: a line
&quot;Requires:  xfce4-settings&quot;
in xfce4-xkb-plugin.spec would solve the case.</thetext>
